summary: Today marks just one month until “Avengers: Endgame” hits theaters. Of course, we know that this film will come with a great...
body:
Today marks just one month until “Avengers: Endgame” hits theaters. Of course, we know that this film will come with a great deal of loss, but now we have seen just how much. In a new set of character posters, we see exactly how wide the loss is in the Marvel Cinematic Universe.

The posters (featured below) feature our surviving heroes in color, with the heroes with lost in the snap in black and gray. This has lead to fans not only realizing just how much Thanos took away, but also exactly who we’re missing. To see the list of the supers taken by the snap, look through the gallery below.

Though, that is not all we got today! We also received a new featurette featuring Chris Evans (Captain America) and Robert Downey Jr. (Iron Man). The featurette deals with a tough topic, the Avengers have lost. Though we are used to our heroes coming out on top, this featurette has made it very clear that the supers we know and love have been beaten. It will definitely be interesting to see how they pick up the pieces around them and try to save the universe!

Marvel Studios’ AVENGERS: ENDGAME releases in U.S. theaters on April 26.

What do you think of the new character posters? Are you excited to see the film next month? Connect with us on Twitter and Facebook to let us know what you think!
